The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Civic 

commissioner Debashis Som on Tuesday dismissed draughtsman Subrata Pal, posted 

at the Behala office, and suspended Srikumar Chakraborty, an inspector of Borough 

I, on charges of corruption. Som took the action on orders from mayor Subrata 

Mukherjee. According to the mayor, Pal had started a construction business in 

the name of his wife and cheated several people who intended to buy flats from 

him. The inspector, Mukherjee said, was suspended because he had mutated a four-cottah 

plot in north Calcutta (3D, Vindhyabasini), purchased by a woman, in the name 

of another person who owns an adjacent plot. The inspector had even refused to 

correct the records when the woman pointed out the irregularity. 

 Long-distance trains from north India continued to arrive late in the city on Tuesday because of fog. The New Delhi-Howrah Rajdhani Express arrived eight hours late, while the New Delhi-Sealdah Rajdhani was nearly 11 hours behind schedule. 

 mong the other trains that ran behind schedule were the Jodhpur Express (two hours 40 minutes), Shipra Express (four hours), Kalka Mail (four hours), Doon Express (nine hours), Mumbai Mail via Allahabad (four hours), Amritsar Mail (four hours) and the Jammu Tawi-Sealdah Express (eight hours). 

 A delegation of the Bidhannagar Welfare Association met civic chairman Dilip Gupta on Tuesday and demanded repair of roads and steps to curb traffic jams and prevent road mishaps. Ramen Das, vice-president of the residents? organisation, said the delegation also demanded construction of a flyover connecting the First Avenue with VIP Road.

 A CPM activist was shot at by a group of criminals in Budge Budge, on the southern fringes of the city, on Tuesday. Police said Buddha Ghosh, 40, was shot from behind when he was returning home in the evening. He was admitted to SSKM Hospital, where his condition was stated to be critical.

 Nasir Hussain, 18, was seriously injured when a Calcutta Municipal Corporation dumper knocked him down. The incident took place around 11.40 am in Garden Reach, when Nasir was crossing the road.

 n another incident, Calcutta Police constable T. Sarker was injured when a speeding bike hit him on NS Road.

 State jails minister Biswanath Chowdhury will meet senior officials of three central jails in the city ? Alipore, Presidency and Dum Dum ? on Wednesday to discuss repair plans. 

 enior public works department engineers, too, will be present at the meeting, to be held at Writers? Buildings.

 Khokan Das and four other members of Choloman Biplabi Sanhati Committee, who were fasting to protest alleged police high-handedness on Naxalites, were arrested on Wednesday. 

 Classes resumed at Kanailal Bhattacharya College, Howrah, on Tuesday after students withdrew their strike, on since December 14. Trouble broke out after a student of BA (pass) complained that she had been molested by a teacher during an educational tour. 

 team from Calcutta University has assured the students that action will be taken against the teacher if he is found guilty. 

